 on critical and comparative studies in a broad range of literary interests, the book sheds light on the emergence of the modern novel in the early modern period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Renaissance.2bisacsh  aAeneid.  aDante.  aDivine Comedy.  aEnglish translation.  aHomer.  aItalian Renaissance prose romance.  aJacopo Caviceo.  aLucrezia Borgia.  aPeregrino.  aVergil.  aearly European novel.  aepic.  ahistory of the novel.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z9783111318264oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079736740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753260440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487532604423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487532604/original  a978-3-11-079736-7  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-127195-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131918-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSPb2023